        <prompt>What was the significance of the "Redemption" period in Texas?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Return to Democratic control and racial restrictions</option>
            <option letter="b">Expansion of civil rights</option>
            <option letter="c">Economic prosperity</option>
            <option letter="d">Educational reform</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Texas's "Redemption" marked the return to Democratic control and implementation of racial restrictions through new laws and constitutional changes.</explanation>
